+# AGENTS.md
+
+## Purpose
+This project contains a Jetson camera driver for Prophesee GENX320 sensor.
+Use this file as the working rules for coding, validation, and consistency.
+
+## Pre-Commit Setup
+Before starting development, install and enable pre-commit in this generated
+project:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m pip install --user pre-commit
+export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
+pre-commit install --install-hooks
+```
+
+Rules:
+- Keep `.pre-commit-config.yaml` enabled; do not bypass hooks by default.
+- If a hook reports issues, fix them and re-run hooks until clean.
+
+## Linting
+Run linting on changed files before finishing work:
+
+```bash
+scripts/driver-dev-tools/bin/lint-c <changed.c> <changed.h>
+scripts/driver-dev-tools/bin/lint-dt <changed.dts> <changed.dtsi>
+scripts/driver-dev-tools/bin/lint-kconfig <Kconfig files>
+scripts/driver-dev-tools/bin/lint-all nvidia-oot hardware scripts
+```
+
+Rules:
+- Treat lint output as gating: fix reported errors and warnings, or document
+  intentional exceptions.
+- Do not assume formatting alone resolves all lint findings.
+- After any modification, run the appropriate linters for the changed files
+  and keep iterating until checks are clean.
+
+## Formatting
+Use the project formatter for C/H files only:
+
+```bash
+scripts/driver-dev-tools/bin/format-c <changed.c> <changed.h>
+```
+
+Rules:
+- Do not run C formatters on device-tree files.
+- Do not hand-format against a different style file.
+- Re-run lint after formatting.
+- If lint still reports issues after formatting, fix them manually.
+- Use a validation loop for changed files:
+  1. run formatter(s) when applicable
+  2. run linter(s)
+  3. fix remaining lint findings manually
+  4. re-run linter(s) until clean
+
+## Consistency Rules
+- Keep sensor naming aligned across:
+  - i2c device ID tables
+  - `i2c_driver.name`
+  - DT `compatible` strings
+- Keep mode ordering aligned between:
+  - driver mode tables (`*_mode_tbls.h`)
+  - DT mode nodes (`mode0`, `mode1`, ...)
+- Keep `remote-endpoint` links consistent in both directions.
+- Resolve remaining template TODO markers before release.
+
+## Documentation
+- Keep project README and build instructions aligned with current behavior.
+- If output paths, module names, or workflows change, update docs in the same
+  change.
+- Build and testing instructions are defined in `README.md`; follow that file
+  strictly when building or testing the driver.
+- If the user asks to build, follow `README.md` build instructions.
+- If any README instruction is unclear, ask the user before taking action.
+- Do not perform actions outside what is explicitly stated in `README.md`
+  without asking the user first.
+
+## Build Confirmation
+- If the user requests a build, do not start immediately.
+- Before running any build command, present a short build summary including:
+  - source/build root path where the build will run
+  - driver/template paths being copied/used
+  - output/artifact paths expected from the build
+  - toolchain identifier and full location/path being used
+  - relevant environment variables or assumptions (for example `L4T_SRC_ROOT`,
+    `TOOLCHAIN_ROOT`, `CROSS_COMPILE`, target JetPack/L4T version)
+- Run a preflight check for required build inputs before final confirmation
+  (for example source tree, toolchain path, required scripts/assets).
+- If any required input is missing, do not ask only for manual paths and stop.
+  Instead:
+  - show exactly what is missing and where it is expected
+  - propose concrete commands to fetch/install/download missing pieces
+  - ask explicit user permission to run those fetch/install commands first
+- If the user approves dependency fetch/setup, request any needed escalation in
+  restricted environments and complete the setup step before build.
+- After dependency setup, present the updated build summary again and ask for
+  final build confirmation.
+- Ask for explicit user confirmation after presenting the summary.
+- Build commands must be executed with escalated privileges.
+- In restricted/sandboxed environments, request escalation approval before
+  running the build.
+- Start the build only after the user confirms.
