+# L4T_DEVELOPMENT
+
+This guide is meant to live in the root of `L4T_SRC_ROOT`.
+Use it for day-to-day development, build, deployment, and validation.
+
+## Setup (Inside `L4T_SRC_ROOT`)
+
+If not already set in your shell:
+
+```bash
+export L4T_SRC_ROOT="${L4T_SRC_ROOT:-$PWD}"
+export TOOLCHAIN_ROOT="${TOOLCHAIN_ROOT:-$HOME/l4t-gcc}"
+export TOOLCHAIN_PREFIX="${TOOLCHAIN_PREFIX:-$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT/aarch64--glibc--stable-2022.08-1/bin/aarch64-buildroot-linux-gnu-}"
+```
+
+Note: once `build_l4t_prepare_environment` succeeds, `scripts/build_l4t.sh`
+stores `TOOLCHAIN_ROOT` in `L4T_SRC_ROOT/.env` for reference.
+If no toolchain argument is provided later, the script checks `.env` for
+`TOOLCHAIN_ROOT`.
+
+## Get Toolchain (If Missing)
+
+If the Bootlin toolchain is not installed yet:
+
+```bash
+mkdir -p "$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT"
+cd "$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT"
+wget https://toolchains.bootlin.com/downloads/releases/toolchains/aarch64/tarballs/aarch64--glibc--stable-2022.08-1.tar.bz2
+tar xf aarch64--glibc--stable-2022.08-1.tar.bz2
+```
+
+Optional check:
+
+```bash
+test -x "${TOOLCHAIN_PREFIX}gcc" && "${TOOLCHAIN_PREFIX}gcc" --version
+```
+
+Alternative (using the helper function in `build_l4t.sh`):
+
+```bash
+cd "$L4T_SRC_ROOT"
+source ./scripts/build_l4t.sh
+build_l4t_download_toolchain "$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT"
+# This also prepares the build environment in the current shell.
+```
+
+Install and enable pre-commit in `L4T_SRC_ROOT`:
+
+```bash
+cd "$L4T_SRC_ROOT"
+python3 -m pip install --user pre-commit
+export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
+pre-commit install --install-hooks
+```
+
+## Build (Recommended: Single Script)
+
+Run from `L4T_SRC_ROOT`:
+
+```bash
+cd "$L4T_SRC_ROOT"
+./scripts/build_l4t.sh "$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT"
+```
+
+Function mode (interactive shell, optional):
+
+```bash
+cd "$L4T_SRC_ROOT"
+source ./scripts/build_l4t.sh "$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT"
+# Sourcing also installs pre-commit hooks.
+
+# In interactive shells, sourcing adds a [L4T-BUILD] prompt prefix.
+# Restore original prompt when done:
+build_l4t_deactivate_environment
+
+# Full build:
