+
+# Or use target commands:
+build kernel
+build modules
+build dtbs
+stage kernel
+stage modules
+stage precommit
+```
+
+Argument notes:
+
+- You can pass `"$HOME/l4t-gcc"` (parent directory), or
+- `"$HOME/l4t-gcc/aarch64--glibc--stable-2022.08-1"` (extracted toolchain directory).
+
+What this script does:
+
+1. Exports `CROSS_COMPILE`, `KERNEL_HEADERS`, and `INSTALL_MOD_PATH`.
+2. Builds kernel image.
+3. Installs kernel/in-tree modules into `rootfs/`.
+4. Builds OOT modules and installs them into `rootfs/`.
+5. Builds DTBs/DTBOs.
+
+Expected outputs:
+
+- Kernel image: `kernel/kernel-jammy-src/arch/arm64/boot/Image`
+- Sensor module: `nvidia-oot/drivers/media/i2c/nv_gen320.ko`
+- DT outputs: `kernel-devicetree/generic-dts/dtbs/*`
+- Overlay DTBOs:
+  - `kernel-devicetree/generic-dts/dtbs/tegra234-p3767-camera-p3768-genx320-A.dtbo`
+  - `kernel-devicetree/generic-dts/dtbs/tegra234-p3767-camera-p3768-genx320-dual.dtbo`
+
+## Build (Manual Commands, Optional)
+
+Use this section only if you do not want to use `build_l4t.sh`.
+
+Set common environment once:
+
+```bash
+cd "$L4T_SRC_ROOT"
+export CROSS_COMPILE="$TOOLCHAIN_PREFIX"
+export KERNEL_HEADERS="$PWD/kernel/kernel-jammy-src"
+export INSTALL_MOD_PATH="${PWD}/rootfs/"
+```
+
+### Build Kernel
+
+```bash
+cd "$L4T_SRC_ROOT"
+make -C kernel
+mkdir -p rootfs/boot
+make install -C kernel
+```
+
+### Build NVIDIA Out-of-Tree Modules
+
+```bash
+cd "$L4T_SRC_ROOT"
+make modules
+mkdir -p rootfs
+make modules_install
+```
+
+### Build DTBs / DTBOs
+
+```bash
+cd "$L4T_SRC_ROOT"
+make dtbs
+```
+
+## Development Loop
+
+For each change:
+
+1. Edit driver/DT files under `nvidia-oot/` and `hardware/`.
+2. Run pre-commit hooks or equivalent lint/format checks.
+3. Build with `./scripts/build_l4t.sh "$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT"` (or manual path).
+4. Deploy/test on target.
+5. Repeat until checks and runtime validation pass.
+
+## GENX320 Transport Configuration
+
+The GENX320 driver reads its streaming transport settings from the base camera
+`.dtsi` files:
+
+- Single camera:
+  `hardware/nvidia/t23x/nv-public/overlay/tegra234-camera-genx320.dtsi`
+- Dual camera:
+  `hardware/nvidia/t23x/nv-public/overlay/tegra234-camera-genx320-dual.dtsi`
+
+At the top of those files, the transport defaults are defined as macros:
+
+```dts
+#define GENX320_TRANSPORT_MODE "variable"
+#define GENX320_TRANSPORT_PACKET_SIZE 1024
+#define GENX320_TRANSPORT_FRAME_SIZE 32
+#define GENX320_TRANSPORT_WINDOW_US 1008
+```
+
+Those macros feed the per-sensor DT properties consumed by the driver:
+
+- `psee,transport-mode`
+  - Valid values: `"variable"` or `"fixed-frame-size"`
+- `psee,transport-packet-size`
+  - Packet payload size in bytes
+  - Valid range: `4..8192`
+  - Must be a multiple of `4`
+- `psee,transport-frame-size`
+  - Packets per frame
+  - Valid range: `1..65535`
+- `psee,transport-window-us`
+  - Frame window in microseconds
+  - Used only in `"variable"` mode
+  - Valid range: `16..65520`
+  - Must be a multiple of `16`
+
+Mode behavior:
+
+- `"variable"`
+  - The driver programs the packet size and frame window.
+  - `psee,transport-window-us` is the active timing control.
+- `"fixed-frame-size"`
+  - The driver programs the packet size and a fixed packets-per-frame count.
+  - `psee,transport-frame-size` is the active frame-size control.
+
+What you need to change:
+
+1. Edit only the `GENX320_TRANSPORT_*` macros at the top of
+   `tegra234-camera-genx320.dtsi` or
+   `tegra234-camera-genx320-dual.dtsi`.
+2. Do not edit the `mode0` geometry fields separately for this purpose.
+
+What those macros control:
+
+- `GENX320_TRANSPORT_PACKET_SIZE`
+  - Becomes the frame width used in `mode0`
+  - Also becomes `line_length`
+- `GENX320_TRANSPORT_FRAME_SIZE`
+  - Becomes the frame height used in `mode0`
+- `GENX320_TRANSPORT_WINDOW_US`
+  - Sets the frame window timing when using `"variable"` mode
+- `GENX320_TRANSPORT_MODE`
+  - Selects whether the stream uses `"variable"` timing or
+    `"fixed-frame-size"`
+
+In short:
+
+- Packet size maps to frame width
+- Number of packets per frame maps to frame height
+- The `.dtsi` already wires those relationships for you through the shared
+  macros
+
+Dual-camera note:
+
+- `tegra234-camera-genx320-dual.dtsi` uses one shared transport macro set for
+  both sensors, so both camera instances will use the same packet/frame
+  configuration unless you split that file further
+
+After changing any of these values:
+
+1. Rebuild DTBs/DTBOs.
+2. Deploy the updated DTB/DTBO to the target.
+3. Reboot before validating capture behavior.
+
+## Deployment Options
+
+### Option 1: Dynamic overlay
+
+1. Copy DTBO to target `/boot`.
+2. Enable with Jetson-IO.
+3. Reboot.
+
+### Option 2: Static main DTB include
+
+Include the current board-specific GENX320 camera DT include in the main board
+DT and rebuild/deploy the DTB:
+
+- Single camera: `tegra234-p3767-camera-genx320.dtsi`
+- Dual camera: `tegra234-p3767-camera-genx320-dual.dtsi`
+
+## Validation / Test
+
+On target:
+
+```bash
+# Device tree presence (path-agnostic: locate node by compatible string)
+DT_BASE=/sys/firmware/devicetree/base
+COMPAT="prophesee,genx320"
+grep -RIlas "$COMPAT" "$DT_BASE" || echo "compatible not found in active DT"
+
+# Optional: print normalized compatible contents for each matched node
+grep -RIlas "$COMPAT" "$DT_BASE" 2>/dev/null | while IFS= read -r compat_file; do
+	printf '%s: ' "${compat_file%/compatible}"
+	tr -d '\0' < "$compat_file"
+	echo
+done
+
+# Driver probe logs
+dmesg | grep -Ei "genx320|camera|i2c"
+
+# Media and video registration
+v4l2-ctl --list-devices
+media-ctl -p
+
+# Basic capture sanity test
+# Do not assume /dev/video0. Pick the node listed for your sensor.
+VIDEO_NODE="<video-node>"
+v4l2-ctl -d "$VIDEO_NODE" --stream-mmap --stream-count=100
+```
+
+## Consistency Rules Before Final Use
+
+1. Keep names aligned across:
+   - `i2c_device_id`
+   - `i2c_driver.name`
+   - DT `.compatible`
+2. Keep mode ordering aligned between:
+   - `genx320_mode_tbls.h` mode enum/map/frame formats
+   - DT mode blocks in `tegra234-camera-genx320.dtsi`
+3. Resolve all template `/*TODO: ...*/` comments.
