diff --git a/nvidia-oot/tools/genx320-ctrl/README.md b/nvidia-oot/tools/genx320-ctrl/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..f76725ecd
--- /dev/null
+++ b/nvidia-oot/tools/genx320-ctrl/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,99 @@
+# GENX320 Control Test Tool
+
+This directory contains a small userspace utility for exercising the custom
+`genx320` V4L2 controls exported by the Orin driver.
+
+Copy the tool sources to the Jetson board and build it there:
+
+```bash
+BOARD=<user>@<board>
+BOARD_DIR=/home/nvidia/genx320-ctrl
+
+scp -r nvidia-oot/tools/genx320-ctrl "$BOARD:/home/nvidia/"
+ssh "$BOARD" "cd '$BOARD_DIR' && make"
+```
+
+
+The tool target the sensor subdevice node, not the capture video
+node. Find it with:
+
+```bash
+v4l2-ctl --list-devices
+media-ctl -p
+```
+
+Typical invocation on the board:
+
+```bash
+cd /home/nvidia/genx320-ctrl
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 list
+```
+
+`metavision_viewer` can keep streaming on the associated `/dev/videoX` node
+while this tool updates the controls on `/dev/v4l-subdevX`.
+
+Sample commands for every exported control:
+
+```bash
+cd /home/nvidia/genx320-ctrl
+
+# List and inspect controls
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 list
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 info evt_format
+
+# Read-only controls
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 get width
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 get height
+
+# Event format
+# Note: the driver rejects evt_format changes while streaming.
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 get evt_format
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set evt_format evt2
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set evt_format evt21
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set evt_format evt3
+
+# ERC controls
+# Set both together because they are clustered in the driver.
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 get erc_enable
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 erc 0 1000000
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 erc 1 1000000
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 erc 1 50000
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 erc 0 50000
+
+# ROI controls
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 get roi_set
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set roi_roni 0
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set roi_roni 1
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 roi-set 0,0,64,64
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 roi-set 0,0,64,64 128,128,32,32
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 button roi_reset
+
+# Pixel mask controls
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 get pxl_set
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 pixel 10 10 0
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 pixel 10 10 1
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 pixel-rect 0 0 32 32 0
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 pixel-rect 0 0 32 32 1
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 pixel-all 0
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 pixel-all 1
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 button pxl_reset
+
+# Bias controls
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 get bias_fo
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 bias-restore
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set bias_fo 10
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set bias_fo 60
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set bias_hpf 10
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set bias_diff_on 70
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set bias_diff 10
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set bias_diff_off 70
+./genx320_ctrl_test -d /dev/v4l-subdev1 set bias_refr 50
+```
+
+Control notes:
+
+- `evt_format` is blocked by the driver while the sensor is streaming.
+- The other GENX320 custom controls are intended to be adjustable while the
+  stream is active.
+- `pixel` and `pixel-rect` read the current pixel grid, modify it in memory,
+  then write the full `pxl_set` payload back through `VIDIOC_S_EXT_CTRLS`.
