@@ -0,0 +1,142 @@
+# GENX320 OpenEB Capture Tool
+
+This directory contains a small OpenEB-based utility for GENX320 with two
+headless modes:
+
+- `record`: record the live camera directly to a native Metavision `RAW` file
+  without a viewer window.
+- `render`: read a `RAW` or `HDF5` event file offline and aggregate events into
+  a single raw `GRAY` frame stream suitable for tools such as Vooya.
+
+## Features
+
+- Headless camera recording through `Camera::start_recording()`.
+- Offline rendering with a configurable aggregation window in microseconds.
+- Dense timeline output: empty aggregation windows are kept in the stream.
+- Single-file grayscale output: one `320x320` `GRAY` frame after another.
+- Offline rendering based on OpenEB frame generation semantics.
+- No GUI or display rendering in the capture path.
+
+## Prerequisites
+
+This tool is intended to be built on a system where OpenEB / Metavision SDK is
+already installed.
+
+The build uses:
+
+- `MetavisionSDK` CMake package
+- `Boost::program_options`
+
+## Build
+
+```bash
+cd genx320-openeb-capture
+make
+```
+
+The resulting binary is `./genx320_openeb_capture`.
+
+## Jetson Note
+
+On the Jetson `tegra-video` V4L2 integration used by this GENX320 driver, you
+should export:
+
+```bash
+export PSEE_VAR_V4L2_BSIZE=1
+```
+
+before live capture.
+
+Why this matters:
+
+- without it, OpenEB may keep the stale tail of the fixed-size V4L2 buffer
+  instead of trimming to the valid EVT payload
+- that can produce very large `RAW` files and
+  `Error TimeHigh discrepancy` during offline decode
+- with it, OpenEB trims the live V4L2 buffer at the EVT end-of-frame marker
+
+This variable is relevant for live camera capture through V4L2. It is not
+needed for offline rendering of an already-correct `RAW` file.
+
+## Record Mode
+
+Record a native Metavision event file from the first available camera:
+
+```bash
+export PSEE_VAR_V4L2_BSIZE=1
+
+./genx320_openeb_capture record \
+  -o fan.raw \
+  --duration-ms 5000
+```
+
+Common options:
+
+- `-o`, `--output`: output `RAW` file path.
+- `-s`, `--serial`: optional camera serial.
+- `-j`, `--input-camera-config`: optional JSON camera settings file to load
+  before recording.
+- `--duration-ms`: optional recording duration in milliseconds. If omitted,
+  recording continues until `Ctrl-C`.
+
+Examples:
+
+```bash
+export PSEE_VAR_V4L2_BSIZE=1
+
+./genx320_openeb_capture record -o capture.raw --duration-ms 10000
+./genx320_openeb_capture record -s "genx320 9-003c" -o capture.raw
+./genx320_openeb_capture record -j settings.json -o capture.raw --duration-ms 5000
+```
+
+Use `-j/--input-camera-config` when you want OpenEB to restore your saved
+biases, ROI, ERC, and other supported live-camera settings immediately after
+opening the camera and before streaming starts. This is important on the V4L2
+backend, where some OpenEB facilities reset certain controls to defaults during
+camera initialization.
+
+## Render Mode
+
+Render a recorded file to a single `GRAY` raw frame stream:
+
+```bash
+./genx320_openeb_capture render \
+  -i fan.raw \
+  -o fan_320x320.raw \
+  --frame-us 10000
+```
+
+Common options:
+
+- `-i`, `--input`: input `RAW` or `HDF5` event file.
+- `-o`, `--output`: output raw grayscale video file.
+- `--frame-us`: aggregation window in microseconds. Default: `10000`.
+
+Examples:
+
+```bash
+./genx320_openeb_capture render -i fan.raw -o fan_320x320.raw
+./genx320_openeb_capture render -i fan.raw -o fan_320x320_200fps.raw --frame-us 5000
+./genx320_openeb_capture render -i fan.hdf5 -o fan_320x320.raw --frame-us 20000
+```
+
+## Visualizing using Vooya
+
+Open the rendered file in Vooya as:
+
+- width: `320`
+- height: `320`
+- format: `8-bit single channel`
+
+## Notes
+
+- In the generated `GRAY` frames:
+  - no recent event in the accumulation window -> mid-gray
+  - positive / rising event -> white
+  - negative / falling event -> black
+- Each pixel shows the most recent event polarity seen in the selected
+  accumulation window.
+- The output keeps the real event timeline. Empty windows are written as
+  background-only frames.
+- On Jetson `tegra-video`, `record` should be run with
+  `PSEE_VAR_V4L2_BSIZE=1`.
